cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.IT 

The paper discusses the application of model-free learning mechanisms in cognitive wireless networks, which involves the intersection of several computer science subfields. The most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as the paper focuses on the application of learning mechanisms in wireless networks. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms, which suggests the category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of cognitive intelligence and self-organization, which are topics in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the improvement of network performance, which suggests the category cs.IT (Information Theory).
